{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"2":{"eng-name":"Prayer (Kitab Al-Salat)","ara-name":"كتاب الصلاة"}},"section_detail":{"2":{"hadithnumber_first":391,"hadithnumber_last":1160,"arabicnumber_first":391,"arabicnumber_last":1160}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":1093,"arabicnumber":1093,"text":"Jabir b. Samurah said:The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to deliver the sermon standing, then he would sit down, then stand and preach standing. If anyone tells you he preached sitting, he is lying. I swear by Allah that I offered along with more than two thousand prayers","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Hasan"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Hasan"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Sahih Lighairihi"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih Muslim (862)"}],"reference":{"book":2,"hadith":704},"chapter":{"id":230,"ara-name":"باب الْخُطْبَةِ قَائِمًا","eng-name":"Giving The Khutbah While Standing","isFirstHadith":true}}]}